%U A395765 7768652131253698010726400000,189329460672170539873521008640000,6200149639791767548556682032578560000,265694561569328384410252384995689103360000
%N A395765 First column of the triangular array with T(0, m) = m! and T(n, m) = T(n - 1, m + 3) - T(n - 1, m + 2).
%C A395765 a(n) is the first entry in the n-th row of a triangular array built from the factorial sequence, where T(0, m) = m! and each subsequent row is obtained by T(n, m) = T(n - 1, m + 3) - T(n - 1, m + 2).
%C A395765 The rows are generated by iterating the operator E^2*Delta, where E is the forward shift operator, E(f(m)) = f(m + 1), and Delta = E - 1 is the forward difference operator. Equivalently, E^2*Delta = E^2*(E - 1) = E^3 - E^2.
%C A395765 This is the (p, q) = (1, 2) case of the family obtained by iterating E^q*Delta^p on the factorial sequence. The case (p, q) = (1, 0) gives the derangement numbers A000166 and the case (p, q) = (1, 1) gives A033815.
%F A395765 Let f(m) = m!. Then:
%F A395765 a(n) = ((E^2*Delta)^n f)(0).
%F A395765 a(n) = Sum_{j=0..n} (-1)^j*binomial(n, j)*(3*n - j)!.
%F A395765 a(n) = Integral_{t=0..oo} t^(2*n)*(t - 1)^n*exp(-t) dt.
%F A395765 More generally, if b_{p, q}(n) = ((E^q*Delta^p)^n f)(0), where f(m) = m!, then b_{p, q}(n) = Integral_{t=0..oo} t^(q*n)*(t - 1)^(p*n)*exp(-t) dt = Sum_{j=0..p*n} (-1)^j*binomial(p*n, j)*((p + q)*n - j)!.
%F A395765 a(n) ~ sqrt(2*Pi) * 3^(3*n + 1/2) * n^(3*n + 1/2) / exp(3*n + 1/3). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 13 2026
%e A395765 First column of
